               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1494" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1494" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1494" type="surname" value="REYNOLDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1494" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD REYNOLDS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in the Commercial-road. On the 10th of April I was employed as waiter at the Prince of Wales public-house at Stepney fair—the prisoner and two or three others came around me, and pushed me about—the prisoner put his hand into my right waistcoat-pocket, and took 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in silver, which I had counted not five minutes before—I saw his hand come out of my pocket, and he passed it to somebody else—I put my hand to my pocket, and the money was gone—I immediately caught hold of him, and said, "You have robbed me "—I held him till the policeman came.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were there not a number of persons scuffling about? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not all of them—there were some pushing about—the prisoner had been drinking—I am certain I was sober—the prisoner came and spoke some nonsense first, and then he and two or three others pushed me about—there were forty or fifty persons present, but not more than three or four standing up about me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1495" type="witnessName">
